        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_arvīston" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>arvīston</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>смесь сена с соломой в измельченном виде</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>chopped hay and straw mixture</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>смесь</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>mixture</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сумятица</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>confusion</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>неразбериха</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>muddle</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">переносно —</note><note
                        type="comment" xml:lang="en">figuratively —</note></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ cardæj nyn arvīston yskodtoj; raxīz æmæ galīw kæm īs, ūj nal
                            zonæm</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>они внесли сумятицу в нашу жизнь; мы уже не знаем, где право, где
                                лево</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they have brought confusion to our lives; we no longer know where is
                                right, where is left</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">По облику -— отглагольное образование: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_a-"/> — преверб, %i-on%i — суффикс, %irvīst%i — прош.
                    причастие от какого-то глагола со значением ‘сечь’, ‘крошить’ (ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>сечка</w></mentioned>). Предполагая закономерную перестановку %irvist%i ←
                    %i*vrīst%i, приходим к <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*braiš-: *brīšta</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">со
                            значением</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">with the
                            meaning</note>
                        <gloss><q>ломать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>крошить</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>vrī-: vrišk-</w>
                        <gloss><q>ломать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 258
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 258 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*braiš-</w></mentioned> представляет удлинение и.е. корня <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*bhrei-</w>
                        <gloss><q>резать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>крошить</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр., который распознается в
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>friare</w>
                        <gloss><q>растирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>разбивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                            ><w>fricare</w>
                        <gloss><q>растирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/>
                        <w>briser</w>
                        <gloss><q>разбивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дробить</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из
                            галльского)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                            Gaulish)</note></mentioned> и пр. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">166
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">166 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). С
                    удлинением %i-n%i мы находим этот же корень в ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_lvynyn"/> ‘стричь’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Formally, a deverbal derivation: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_a-"/> is a preverb, %i-on%i is a suffix, and %irvīst%i is a
                    past participle of some verb with the meaning ‘shred’, ‘chop’ (cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>сечка</w>
                        <gloss><q>chaff</q></gloss></mentioned>). Assuming the natural alternation
                    %irvist%i ← %i*vrīst%i, we reconstruct <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*braiš-: *brīšta</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">со
                            значением</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">with the
                            meaning</note>
                        <gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>chop</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>vrī-: vrišk-</w>
                        <gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 258
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 258 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*braiš-</w></mentioned> is elongation of the Indo-European root
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*bhrei-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cut</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>chop</q></gloss></mentioned> etc., which is recognized in
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>friare</w>
                        <gloss><q>grind</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                            ><w>fricare</w>
                        <gloss><q>grind</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/>
                        <w>briser</w>
                        <gloss><q>break up</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fraction</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из
                            галльского)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                            Gaulish)</note></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">166
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">166 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
                    With the elongation %i-n%i, we find the same root in <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_lvynyn"/> ‘cut’.</etym>
            </entry>
